-- Legrand Nine-Month Net Income Rises 60%; Operating Margin Target Raised
-- B y   P h i l   S e r a f i n o
-- 2010-11-04T06:30:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-04/legrand-nine-month-net-income-rises-60-operating-margin-target-raised.html
Legrand SA said net income rose 60
percent to 319.2 million euros in the first nine months of the
year. Sales climbed 7.5 percent to 2.87 billion euros. The
company raised its full-year target for adjusted operating
margin to 20 percent from over 19 percent previously.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Phil Serafino at 
 pserafino@bloomberg.net  